      "message": "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI tried building this here and it failed\r\n\r\nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master-fc15/34/arch=x86_64,build_type=client,distro=fc15,ib_stack=inkernel/console\r\n\r\nIt could be a builder issue, but worth understanding.\r\n\r\nAlso I had to fetch the rpm's for the kernel by hand. I have a feeling that el5/el6 lbuilds fetch the rpms themselves (I could be wrong). Brian probably knows.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "fce67219adfcd997bb584ca6339ebd03c02a0422",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-06 13:05:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nPlease Skype me when you push the next build. I have to kick off this build by hand.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "715f2e36de4e964874d3f5c8e193accebc7ebfd7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-06 13:21:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-master-fc15/arch/x86_64/build_type/client/distro/fc15/ib_stack/inkernel/BUILD/BUILD/lustre-2.3.50/lustre/include/linux/lustre_compat25.h:290:14: error: 'struct vfsmount' has no member named 'mnt_devname'\n\nLooks like the kernel patches need a bit more work.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "f02eb7296f224c90f29782744346f16a0e26788a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-06 16:27:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nPlease reconsider your inspection. This patch just intend let autobuild works well. The mnt_devname build problem will fixed by other patch. It not relate to any kernel patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "6bb2bfc2186c188da840933fac6af6f0e91f04b7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-06 20:41:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nWhy not commit the kernel patch changes together with the lbuild changes (so that they are all one logical piece) rather than breaking them up?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "70b11fd1fd14514a1dd926b46a4a6946ddfcbbdc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-06 21:27:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThis is a patchless build. Doesn't need any kernel patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "06ef130810063a7c2d49fcad1ea74ff9c0b98cb0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-07 01:24:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI would have thought my meaning was clear, but of course I meant s/patches/kernel compatibility/.\n\nTo be perfectly clear, why not put *everything* needed to support a successful FC15 build and run into the same patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "048cef2ef4a52a070bc94060a74b6a9449e210d1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-07 04:12:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nWhy you think we should push everything in one patch? FC15 suppport need a few patches to work. And they are relate to different component. This just for build part. This is not enough clear?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "39c5ad8e03fb238cef4df02e46a7cdea4cadb398",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-07 14:30:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: No score\n\nI (we) think if this patch requires other patches then they should be pushed first. This patch serves no purpose on its own other than to potentially confuse others.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
