        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-07 21:00:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nLooks like the FC15 compiler is being more picky (and rightfully so):\n\nlustre/fld/lproc_fld.c:169:26: error: variable 'info' set but not used\nlustre/llite/vvp_io.c:92:6: error: variable 'result' set but not used\n\nThis is true for both cases.\n\nThese defects will need to be fixed before the FC15 build will complete.  I'm not sure if it's kosher to just lump them into this patch or whether they should be put into a separate, dependent patch complete with their own ticket.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
